# Order / Payment / Inventory Constraints

## Order status
Only use:
- NEW
- PAID
- SHIPPED
- FINISHED
- CANCELLED
- CLOSED

## Payment status
Only use:
- UNPAID
- PAID
- FAIL

## Order flow
Allowed transitions:
- NEW -> PAID / CANCELLED / CLOSED
- PAID -> SHIPPED
- SHIPPED -> FINISHED

## Submit order
Must include:
- validate address
- validate selected cart items
- validate product and sku status
- re-calculate amount from DB
- lock stock with conditional update
- create order
- create order items
- write stock log
- write order operation log
- remove participated cart items
- send timeout MQ after transaction commit

## Payment callback
Must include:
- signature validation placeholder if actual SDK not yet integrated
- idempotent processing
- update payment record
- update order status
- confirm stock deduction
- write logs
- send async message after transaction commit

## Inventory
Use conditional SQL updates.
If affected rows == 0, throw exception and rollback.
